.SH "NAME"
pix\-alias \- convert an image from pix format to Alias(tm) pix format
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBpix\-alias\fP [\-s \fIsquaresize\fP] [\-w \fIfile_width\fP] [\-n \fIfile_height\fP] < \fIBRLpixfile\fP > \fIALIASpixfile\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
\fBpix\-alias\fP converts the (BRL) \fIpix(5)\fP format file on the
standard input to an \fIAlias pix\fP format file on the standard output.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.sp
\fB\-n\fP \fIfile_height\fP
.RS 4
tells \fBpix\-alias\fP that the input is
\fIfile_height\fP scanlines tall
.RE
.sp
\fB\-w\fP \fIfile_width\fP
.RS 4
tells \fBpix\-alias\fP that the input is
\fIfile_width\fP pixels wide
.RE
.sp
\fB\-s\fP \fIsquaresize\fP
.RS 4
sets both the width and the height for the input
to be \fIsquaresize\fP
.RE
